</li></ul></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MegaManX" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MegaManX">Mega Man X</a></em>'s Sting Chameleon uses his tongue to hang from the ceiling and as a nasty fast <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhipItGood" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhipItGood">whip.</a>
</li><li> The Licker enemy in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ResidentEvil2" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ResidentEvil2">Resident Evil 2</a></em>, <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ResidentEvil5" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ResidentEvil5">Resident Evil 5</a></em> and various other games. Its signature attack is using an absurdly long tongue to whip anything it wants to attack, driving it with enough force to impale a prey item with it. They are heavily mutated T-Virus infected humans.
</li><li> Level 3 of <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/GhostsNGoblins" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/GhostsNGoblins">Ghouls'n Ghosts</a></em> has extensible monster tongues that are used as platforms.
</li><li> Volvidon and Baruragaru from <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MonsterHunter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MonsterHunter">Monster Hunter</a></em>. The latter even uses it to suck blood.
</li><li> Your goat in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/GoatSimulator" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/GoatSimulator">Goat Simulator</a></em>. One mutator ("Italian Dinosaur Goat") even allows it to mimic Yoshi by producing "watermelon bombs" from almost anything it licks.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Gigantic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Gigantic">Gigantic</a></em> has Wu, a frog-like <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WarriorMonk" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WarriorMonk">Warrior Monk</a> who uses his long tongue in tandem with his martial art skills. His Togue Lash ability can be used to pull enemies towards him from far away.
</li><li> In <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/TheElderScrolls" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/TheElderScrolls">The Elder Scrolls</a></em> series, Hungers are a form of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OurDemonsAreDifferent" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OurDemonsAreDifferent">lesser Daedra</a> which are very similar in appearance to the "alien-style" <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Chupacabra" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Chupacabra">Chupacabra</a>, complete with claws, spikes, and a "sucker" mouth. They have extremely long, weaponized tongues.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Persona5" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Persona5">Persona 5</a></em>: Asmodeus, boss of the first Palace, is a giant version of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DirtyOldMan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DirtyOldMan">Mr. Kamoshida</a> with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MultiArmedAndDangerous" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MultiArmedAndDangerous">extra arms</a> and a gigantic, creepy tongue that he uses in some attacks.
</li></ul></div>
<p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder15');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Web Animation&nbsp;</div><div id="folder15" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;">
<ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/CharlieTheUnicorn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/CharlieTheUnicorn">Charlie the Unicorn</a>'s "friends" have long, prehensile tongues... <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Squick" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Squick">Squick</a>!
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/Blockhead" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/Blockhead">Blockhead</a></em>
</li><li> Sniffles, a remarkably clever anteater in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/HappyTreeFriends" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/HappyTreeFriends">Happy Tree Friends</a></em> obviously makes use of this trope. However, it is often attacked by the Ant Family in horrifyingly sadistic ways.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/Dreamscape" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/Dreamscape">Dreamscape</a></em>: CHEN has one. He is a chameleon after all. He can even use it like a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GrappleMove" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GrappleMove">Grapple Move</a> or a fist!
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/DSBTInsaniT" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/DSBTInsaniT">DSBT InsaniT</a></em>: Pangle the pangolin has a tongue long enough for Fire Guy to use as a platform.
</li><li> Ceriazibus from <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/SockSeries" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/SockSeries">the Sock series</a> have tongues so long that it can wrap them around on of it's head (it have three of them) multiple times and it's so sharp that it can <strong>decapitate</strong> itself.
</li></ul></div>
<p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder16');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Web Comics&nbsp;</div><div id="folder16" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;">
<ul><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/ByTheTail" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/ByTheTail">By the Tail</a></em>: Echo has a rather long tongue, her being a bat and all.
</li><li> "Legs" from <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/SchlockMercenary" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/SchlockMercenary">Schlock Mercenary</a></em> is an armless, wingless<span class="notelabel" onclick="togglenote('note089v9');"><sup>note&nbsp;</sup></span><span id="note089v9" class="inlinefolder" isnote="true" onclick="togglenote('note089v9');" style="cursor:pointer;font-size:smaller;display:none;">vestigial stubs, technically</span> quasi-bird alien, who possesses a several-yards-long prehensile tongue. It comes in handy surprisingly often.
<ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IncrediblyLamePun" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IncrediblyLamePun">Especially since she often uses it in place of hands.</a>
</li></ul></li><li> Rare female example with <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/GaiGin" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/GaiGin">Gai Gin</a></em>'s Gin, <a class="urllink" href="http://www.gai-gin.com/comic_0177.shtml">apparently<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>.
</li><li> <a class="urllink" href="http://www.schoolbites.net/d/20100122.html">Fujiko<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> of <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/SchoolBites" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/SchoolBites">School Bites</a></em>.
</li><li> <a class="urllink" href="http://wapsisquare.com/comic/tipofhertongue/">Monica<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> of <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/WapsiSquare" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/WapsiSquare">Wapsi Square</a></em>.
<ul><li> Although <a class="urllink" href="http://wapsisquare.com/comic/get-a-room/">it may be slightly exaggerated here<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>.
</li></ul></li><li> Ben from <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/GoblinHollow" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/GoblinHollow">Goblin Hollow</a></em> can lick his own eyebrow. Justified since he's a bear. <a class="urllink" href="http://www.rhjunior.com/goblin-hollow-0330/">It causes an interesting reaction when the cousin of his future wife witnesses it.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>
</li><li> A <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/GirlGenius" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/GirlGenius">Girl Genius</a></em> side story shows that Maxim can lick bloody wounds that are nowhere near his face. The fangirls were intrigued.
</li><li> <a class="urllink" href="http://hexenringe.blogspot.jp/2013/10/002-prologue-2.html">The Blarg<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> from <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/Hexenringe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/Hexenringe">Hexenringe</a></em> has a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Kaiju" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Kaiju">Kaiju-sized</a> frog tongue.
</li><li> In <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/TowerOfGod" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/TowerOfGod">Tower of God</a></em>, Ren's tongues (plural) aren't as long as the other examples on this page but are still about half the length of his body. Also <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SnicketWarningLabel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SnicketWarningLabel">you do not want</a> to see them.
</li><li> In <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/ElGoonishShive" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/ElGoonishShive">El Goonish Shive</a></em>, Nanase's gecko form <a class="urllink" href="http://egscomics.com/egsnp/nanasecraft-14">has one<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, which <a class="urllink" href="http://egscomics.com/egsnp/nanasecraft-20">comes in handy<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> when she needs an alternative way to grab on to something making it a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MultipurposeTongue" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MultipurposeTongue">Multipurpose Tongue</a>.
</li><li> In <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/KevinAndKell" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/KevinAndKell">Kevin &amp; Kell</a></em>, Carla the chameleon is just a baby, but her sticky tongue can already extend many times the length of the rest of her.
</li></ul></div>
<p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder17');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Web Original&nbsp;</div><div id="folder17" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;">
<ul><li> In <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Twig" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Twig">Twig</a></em>, Helen, who is notable for looking human only to lure in prey and practice her acting skills, occasionally demonstrates the ability to extend her tongue well beyond what's possible for humans so she can lick things. When Sylvester catches her tongue after she tries to lick him, she demonstrates that it's also prehensile.
</li></ul></div>
